5:
All right. That should be enough
meat and veggies to last us a
couple days at least.
8:
Hehe... My dear hazubando to be is
quite the chef! How delightful.
9:
And such a creative one, too! I've
never seen such exotic dishes...
13:
Exotic? S-sorry, did they not agree
with your palate?
16:
No, not at all! Where I come from,
such attention to flavor and
presentation is often considered to
be unnecessary.
22:
The people of Palpebra are always
focused on their worldly pleasures.
24:
But lately, I feel like I'm starting to
understand why...
27:
It seems you've taken a liking to life
outside your village, huh?
30:
It haaaaas been rather pleasant,
yes, but...
32:
The presence of sprites is so faint
here...
35:
The people here have such little
respect for the sprites—so many
nonbelievers, it's unbelievable!
38:
Well, you know how it is here... The
sprites don't really show up.
41:
I just know that if you come to my
village, Alk, that you and the sprites
would get along famously!
45:
That reminds me—wanna swing by
the Guild? I need to buy some
sundries for the Kaleidoscope.
50:
Thank ya kindly, Alk! I'll have your
order delivered to Lelucia shortly.
53:
Somebody, anybody! Does anyone
have Masurel's medicinal herbs?
56:
My child has a terrible fever... I need
to get my hands on some soon!
58:
Calm down, buddy. If you're lookin'
for medicine, go find a doctor—
60:
I've already tried! But the
apothecary and clinics were all
cleaned out today! Please... At this
rate...
64:
Please, anybody!
Damn... This was my last hope!
67: Alk, do you know about this herb?
71:
Hmm... It's a rare herb that can only
be found on the highest of cliffsides.
A three-day journey from here, I'd
say.
75:
Of course, if there were a way to fly
there, it'd be a much shorter journey,
but—
79:
This sounds like the perfect time to
show them to the power of the
sprites!
83:
Wait... Yeah! With your power of
flight, getting those herbs would be
a cinch!
89:
Right. You'll need me to tell you
which herb it is, huh?
95:
We're lifting off, so hold on to me
reeeeeal nice and tight, okay?
102:
Give me a nice good squeeze... You
wouldn't want to fall, would you?
112:
Really? I thought you said the wind
did most of the heavy lifting...
128:
If I wanted to, I could change course
any second and take you to my
village, you know?
135:
Of course not!
This time, at least.
138:
We have a child to save, after all.
Time is of the essence!
146:
We'll surely be able to save that
poor child with this.
153:
The ones who should be thankful
are that man and his child.
156:
I mean, you did this because you
wanted to save them, right?
158:
Not particularly. I was merely
fulfilling the role bestowed upon me
by the sprites.
161:
Even though they weren't from your
village?
164:
It was an opportunity to show the
nonbelievers the power of the
sprites.
174:
Now all is left is a geeeentle glide all
the way back to Palpebra.
175:
That being said, be careful not to...
fall off!
179:
Wh-what part of this is supposed to
be gentle?
182:
Hehe... If you're going to be my
hazubando one day, you'd better
get used to at least THIS much
turbulence!
